        </p>

        <h2 className="mt-10 text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold">Why Waterproof Deck Coatings Matter</h2>
        <p>
          A deck faces weather all year. The hot sun dries it out. Hard rain soaks it. Wind blows dirt and dust. These things break down the wood or concrete. If your deck has no coating, the damage grows fast. Water makes small cracks bigger. Mold grows where it stays wet too long. Wood starts to rot.
        </p>
