        <p>A good deck coating must do a few things:</p>
        <ul className="list-disc pl-6">
          <li>Keep out water</li>
          <li>Stand up to sun and heat</li>
          <li>Resist cracking or peeling</li>
          <li>Provide safe traction when wet</li>
          <li>Look good and match your home</li>
        </ul>
        <p className="mt-4">Now we will talk about the kinds of coatings most people choose.</p>

        <h3>Liquid Rubber Coating</h3>
        <p>
          Liquid rubber feels like thick paint when it goes on. When it dries, it feels soft and rubbery. It is flexible. That means it can stretch a little if the deck moves. It fills small cracks. It covers the surface in a smooth layer.
        </p>
        <p className="font-semibold mt-2">Pros</p>
        <ul className="list-disc pl-6">
          <li>Easy to apply with brush or roller</li>
          <li>Adheres to wood and concrete</li>
          <li>Great water barrier for rainy areas</li>
          <li>Flexes with deck movement</li>
        </ul>
        <p className="font-semibold mt-3">Cons</p>
        <ul className="list-disc pl-6">
          <li>Softer feel underfoot; not a hard finish</li>
          <li>Can wear faster in high‑traffic spots</li>
          <li>Finish can look dull over time</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Polyurethane Deck Coating</h3>
        <p>
          Polyurethane is harder. When it dries, it makes a strong, glossy surface. It is good against sun damage. It lasts a long time. It protects well against water and heat.
        </p>
        <p className="font-semibold mt-2">Pros</p>
        <ul className="list-disc pl-6">
          <li>Very durable and glossy finish</li>
          <li>Excellent UV and heat resistance</li>
          <li>Handles heavy foot traffic</li>
        </ul>
        <p className="font-semibold mt-3">Cons</p>
        <ul className="list-disc pl-6">
          <li>Less flexible—can crack if wood moves</li>
          <li>Stronger odor during application</li>
          <li>Longer dry time and needs careful technique</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Acrylic Deck Coating</h3>
        <p>
          Acrylic coatings are also common. They go on like paint. They dry fast. They are water-based. That means less smell. Acrylic coatings are good at resisting sun damage. They come in many colors.
        </p>
        <p className="font-semibold mt-2">Pros</p>
        <ul className="list-disc pl-6">
          <li>Fast drying and low odor</li>
          <li>Good UV resistance</li>
          <li>Wide color selection</li>
        </ul>
        <p className="font-semibold mt-3">Cons</p>
        <ul className="list-disc pl-6">
          <li>Less durable than polyurethane</li>
          <li>Can peel sooner in heavy rain or ponding water</li>
        </ul>

